body:
This *PR* applies [Traute](http://traute.oss.harmonysoft.tech/) *javac* plugin to the project. It enhances compilation process in a way to insert *null*-checks into resulting bytecode based on source code annotations.  

Let's check [LocalProcessLauncher](https://github.com/apache/geode/blob/develop/geode-core/src/main/java/org/apache/geode/internal/process/LocalProcessLauncher.java#L66):  

*Source code before*  

```java
LocalProcessLauncher(final File pidFile, final boolean force)
    throws FileAlreadyExistsException, IOException, PidUnavailableException {
  notNull(pidFile, "Invalid pidFile '" + pidFile + "' specified");
    
  this.pid = identifyPid();
  this.pidFile = pidFile;
  writePid(force);
}
```  

*Source code after*  

```java
LocalProcessLauncher(@NonNull final File pidFile, final boolean force)
    throws FileAlreadyExistsException, IOException, PidUnavailableException {
  this.pid = identifyPid();
  this.pidFile = pidFile;
  writePid(force);
}
```  

Resulting bytecode looks like if it's compiled from the source below:  

```java
LocalProcessLauncher(@NonNull final File pidFile, final boolean force)
    throws FileAlreadyExistsException, IOException, PidUnavailableException {
  if (pidFile == null) {
    throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid pidFile 'null' specified");
  }
  this.pid = identifyPid();
  this.pidFile = pidFile;
  writePid(force);
}
```  

*Bytecode*  

```
javap -c ./geode-core/build/classes/main/org/apache/geode/internal/process/LocalProcessLauncher.class
...
  org.apache.geode.internal.process.LocalProcessLauncher(java.io.File, boolean) throws org.apache.geode.internal.process.FileAlreadyExistsException, java.io.IOException, org.apache.geode.internal.process.PidUnavailableException;
    Code:
       0: aload_0
       1: invokespecial #2                  // Method java/lang/Object."<init>":()V
       4: aload_1
       5: ifnonnull     18
       8: new           #3                  // class java/lang/IllegalArgumentException
      11: dup
      12: ldc           #4                  // String Invalid pidFile 'null' specified
      14: invokespecial #5                  // Method java/lang/IllegalArgumentException."<init>":(Ljava/lang/String;)V
      17: athrow
       ...
```  

Benefits:  
* less boilerplate
* the code is better documented
* it's easier to add new checks (just annotate target method parameters/return values by the *NonNull* or, alternatively, [specify non-null by default](http://traute.oss.harmonysoft.tech/core/javac/#72-notnullbydefault-annotations))
